OL,3,C'I was struggling to breathe': Fire
OL,4,Cbrigade's warning over cleaning
OL,5,Cproducts
OL,7,F"It was scary not being able to
OL,8,Fbreathe properly."
OL,10,FMr Karma said he was "surprised" to
OL,11,Fsee firefighters with breathing
OL,12,Fapparatus attend the incident, not
OL,13,Fknowing the severity of the fumes.
OL,15,F"I'd advise anyone who does the
OL,16,Fcleaning, and uses products, to always
OL,17,Fread the label. This was a scary
OL,18,Fexperience, and I would not want
OL,19,Fanyone else to go through it," Mr
OL,20,FKarma warns.
